How to Invest with Roofstock





















Find it!







Use our Tools & Analytics: Filters, alerts, advisor picks, market analyses, certification and diligence documents such as inspection reports, lease reports, financial calculator, maps, photos, and more
Work with one of our expert Advisors to help refine your strategy or pick a property

























Lock it!







Put your property in the cart. You can put it in contract right away at list price, or on some properties, you can make an offer to try and get a better deal
To accelerate the process, include how you’d like to hold title and if you are using financing, send us your pre-approval letter via email
Pay the Marketplace Fee (0.5% of the sale price) using a credit card at check out 1

























Buy it!






Escrow is the period when financing, insurance and documents are finalized leading up to the transaction. Our service and transaction team will work with you and the seller to complete the transaction within 30 days.

Sign the Purchase & Sale Agreement (PSA) using your electronic signature within 24 hours of receiving it in your email 2
Send your Earnest Money Deposit (EMD) of $1,500 to the title company within 3 days of signing PSA; this is your down payment 3
Finalize your Financing, Insurance and Property Manager (you will need to pay for any appraisal or inspection required by your lender or insurer; the lease and tenant will be transferred to your new property manager)
Sign your Closing Documents & Wire funds to complete the transaction



























Cash it!







Begin receiving income from your investment
Use our online dashboard to monitor your investment





























Still have questions?
Give us a call at 800-339-8511. We’re happy to talk you through it.


The Marketplace Fee is half of one percent of the sales price of the house. Upon payment of the fee, the property is marked as “sale pending” on the marketplace. The Marketplace Fee is not refundable. It is free to make an offer; the Marketplace fee is only applied if your offer is accepted. 
The Purchase and Sale Agreement is the official legal contract between the buyer and the seller and constitutes the opening of the escrow process. All terms for the purchase and sale of the property are outlined in the contract. The specific items in this contract vary by state. 
Earnest Money is a deposit that is made by the buyer as a display of good faith in the transaction. It is held by the Title company, and the funds will be used as part of the buyer’s down payment or closing costs when the transaction is finalized. EMD is either refundable to the buyer or retainable by the seller under the terms outlined in the PSA and refunds are administered by the Title Company. If the EMD is not received within 3 days of signing the PSA, the property will be returned to the marketplace.































